==English==

===Etymology===
*from Greek roots παντ- 'all, every' and γραφ- 'to write'  from their original use for copying writing

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A mechanical [[linkage]] connected in a special manner based on [[parallelogram]]s so that they move in a fixed relationship to each other.  Originally used to copy drawings or writing by [[tracing]] with a pointer at one location on the pantograph causing a pen or pencil at another point to make the same pattern, possibly [[enlarged]] or [[shrunk]].

